Package: nfc-fido-pam
Version: @VER@-1
Architecture: all
Maintainer: dapperdivers <derek.mackley@hotmail.com>
Depends: python3 (>= 3.9), python3-fido2 (>= 1.0), python3-pyscard, libpam-modules, pcscd
Recommends: nfc-nci-pcsc, opensc
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/dapperdivers/nfc-fido-pam
Description: PAM authentication with a FIDO2 NFC authenticator over PC/SC
 Authenticate (login, sudo, screen unlock) by tapping a FIDO2 NFC authenticator -
 an NFC implant, a contactless security key, or a phone - read over PC/SC.
 .
 Ships nfc-fido-verify, a standalone verifier that performs a fresh-challenge
 CTAP2 get_assertion against an enrolled credential and exits 0 on a valid tap,
 plus nfc-fido-enroll to register a credential. Wire it into PAM with the stock
 pam_exec module; the helper-process design means even a PAM client that cannot
 do PC/SC in-process (e.g. a Nix-built lock screen) can authenticate.
 .
 No standard PAM module does FIDO2 over NFC/PC-SC (pam_u2f is USB-HID only), so
 this verifier fills that gap using the python-fido2 PC/SC backend.
